$ SQL Server - system base table: sys.sysprivs

`sys.sysprivs` lists → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/database or server-level permissions. (Server-level permissions are stored in the → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/system-databases/master[master database]). ☰ ✗

`sys.sysprivs` is the underlying system base table from which the view → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/database_permissions[`sys.database_permissions`] selects


sa:
  `sys.sysprivs` is a → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/system-base-tables[system base table], thus it needs a
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/dedicated-administrator-connection[dedicated administrator connection] to select from it.
